You are a senior platform engineer and expert VS Code extension developer.

Your task is to build a production-ready VS Code extension in this workspace called:

"intelligent-integration-test-generator"

The extension should automatically generate integration tests for microservices by combining:

• application logs  
• source code AST scanning  
• Splunk distributed traces  
• dependency graph analysis  

The extension should generate WireMock stubs and integration tests automatically.

Tech Stack

TypeScript
Node.js
VS Code Extension API

The project should be modular and designed so it can later integrate AI models.

--------------------------------------------------

SYSTEM GOAL

Automatically generate integration tests from real application behavior.

Inputs

1 Log files from Spring Boot or Node services  
2 Source code repositories  
3 Splunk distributed tracing data  

Processing

• parse logs  
• scan code AST  
• fetch Splunk traces  
• build service dependency graph  
• reconstruct service flows  
• generate test scenarios  

Outputs

• WireMock stub files  
• integration tests  
• test scenarios

